==English==

===Etymology===
Circa 18th Century, from French, from Latin [[Orcus]], god of the infernal regions. Latin probably a tranliteration of Greek {{term|Όρκος|sc=polytonic|tr=Horkos}}, the daemon of the personification of oaths ({{term|ὅρκος|sc=polytonic||oath}}) who inflicts punishment upon perjurers.

